item.title: CVE-2018-3861|2024-08-05T04:57:24.267Z -- talos -- computerinsel%20photoline
item.description: A specially crafted TIFF image processed via the application can lead to an out-of-bounds write, overwriting arbitrary data. An attacker can deliver a TIFF image to trigger this vulnerability and gain code execution.

item.title: CVE-2018-3886|2024-08-05T04:57:24.247Z -- talos -- computerinsel%20photoline
item.description: A memory corruption vulnerability exists in the PCX-parsing functionality of Computerinsel Photoline 20.53. A specially crafted PCX image processed via the application can lead to an out-of-bounds write, overwriting arbitrary data. An attacker can deliver a PCX image to trigger this vulnerability and gain code execution.
